Imports System

Module LionFeedingTimes
    ' Computes the feeding times for lions in a circular arrangement.
    ' The function returns an array where each element represents the time (in minutes)
    ' when the corresponding lion will be fed for the first time.
    ' The feeding starts at lion 'a' and proceeds in a circular manner.
    Function FeedingTimes(n As Integer, a As Integer) As Integer()
        Dim times(n - 1) As Integer
        For i As Integer = 0 To n - 1
            times((a - 1 + i) Mod n) = i
        Next
        Return times
    End Function
End Module

Imports System
Imports System.Collections.Generic

Module SquareDigitPermutations
    ' Counts the number of perfect squares that can be formed by permuting the digits of the input string.
    ' The input string represents a number with 'n' digits (including leading zeros).
    Function CountSquarePermutations(n As Integer, s As String) As Integer
        ' Initialize a count array to track the frequency of each digit (0-9)
        Dim count(9) As Integer
        For Each c As Char In s
            count(Convert.ToInt32(c.ToString())) += 1
        Next

        ' Calculate the maximum possible square root for an n-digit number
        Dim maxI As Integer = CInt(Math.Floor(Math.Sqrt(Math.Pow(10, n) - 1)))

        ' Count the number of zeros in the input string
        Dim targetZeros As Integer = count(0)

        ' Use a HashSet to store unique perfect squares that match the digit counts
        Dim seen As New HashSet(Of Integer)()

        For i As Integer = 0 To maxI
            Dim x As Integer = i * i
            Dim sRaw As String = x.ToString()
            Dim lenRaw As Integer = sRaw.Length

            ' Skip if the raw string is longer than n digits
            If lenRaw > n Then Continue For

            ' Count zeros in the current square number
            Dim zerosInX As Integer = sRaw.Count(Function(c) c = "0"c)
            Dim paddingZeros As Integer = n - lenRaw

            ' Check if zeros match the target count (including padding zeros)
            If zerosInX + paddingZeros <> targetZeros Then Continue For

            ' Pad the number with leading zeros to make it n digits long
            Dim sPadded As String = sRaw.PadLeft(n, "0"c)

            ' Create a candidate count array for the padded number
            Dim candidate(9) As Integer
            For Each c As Char In sPadded
                candidate(Convert.ToInt32(c.ToString())) += 1
            Next

            ' If the candidate matches the original count, add to the set
            If candidate.SequenceEqual(count) Then
                seen.Add(x)
            End If
        Next

        Return seen.Count
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module MaxPositiveSubarraySum
    ' Finds the maximum sum of any contiguous subarray with a positive net effect.
    '
    ' Parameters:
    '   n - Number of elements in the array.
    '   arr - Array of integers representing spell effects.
    '
    ' Returns:
    '   Integer representing the maximum possible positive net effect of any subarray.
    Function MaxPositiveSubarraySum(n As Integer, arr As Integer()) As Integer
        Dim maxCurrent As Integer = 0
        Dim maxGlobal As Integer = 0
        
        For Each num As Integer In arr
            maxCurrent = Math.Max(0, maxCurrent + num)
            maxGlobal = Math.Max(maxGlobal, maxCurrent)
        Next
        
        Return maxGlobal
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module MaxNumberGenerator
    ' Generates the maximum possible number by performing at most two swaps of digits
    ' in the input string. The function considers all possible pairs of swaps.
    Function GenerateMaxNumber(s As String) As Integer
        Dim digits As Char() = s.ToCharArray()
        Dim maxNum As Integer = 0
        Dim n As Integer = digits.Length
        
        ' First swap
        For firstI As Integer = 0 To n - 1
            For firstJ As Integer = firstI + 1 To n - 1
                ' Perform first swap
                Dim swapped1 As Char() = DirectCast(digits.Clone(), Char())
                swapped1(firstI) = digits(firstJ)
                swapped1(firstJ) = digits(firstI)
                
                ' Second swap
                For secondI As Integer = 0 To n - 1
                    For secondJ As Integer = secondI + 1 To n - 1
                        ' Perform second swap
                        Dim swapped2 As Char() = DirectCast(swapped1.Clone(), Char())
                        swapped2(secondI) = swapped1(secondJ)
                        swapped2(secondJ) = swapped1(secondI)
                        
                        ' Convert to number and update max
                        Dim currentNum As Integer = Integer.Parse(New String(swapped2))
                        If currentNum > maxNum Then
                            maxNum = currentNum
                        End If
                    Next
                Next
            Next
        Next
        
        Return maxNum
    End Function
End Module

Imports System
Imports System.Collections.Generic

Module PostfixEvaluator
    ' Evaluates the given postfix expression and returns the result as a Double
    ' The expression should be space-separated numbers and operators (+, -, *, /)
    Function EvaluatePostfix(expression As String) As Double
        Dim stack As New Stack(Of Double)
        
        ' Tokenize the input expression by splitting on spaces
        Dim tokens As String() = expression.Split(New Char() {" "c}, StringSplitOptions.RemoveEmptyEntries)
        
        ' Process each token in the expression
        For Each token As String In tokens
            If token = "+" Then
                Dim b As Double = stack.Pop()
                Dim a As Double = stack.Pop()
                stack.Push(a + b)
            ElseIf token = "-" Then
                Dim b As Double = stack.Pop()
                Dim a As Double = stack.Pop()
                stack.Push(a - b)
            ElseIf token = "*" Then
                Dim b As Double = stack.Pop()
                Dim a As Double = stack.Pop()
                stack.Push(a * b)
            ElseIf token = "/" Then
                Dim b As Double = stack.Pop()
                Dim a As Double = stack.Pop()
                stack.Push(a / b)
            Else
                ' Push operand to stack (convert token to Double)
                stack.Push(Double.Parse(token))
            End If
        Next
        
        ' The final result should be the only element in the stack
        Return stack.Pop()
    End Function
End Module

Imports System
Imports System.Collections.Generic

Module KnightMovesCalculator
    ' Calculates all valid moves for a knight-like piece with custom (a, b) movement rules.
    ' The piece starts at a given position on an 8x8 chessboard.
    ' Returns the count of valid moves and the sorted list of moves.
    Sub CalculateValidMoves(a As Integer, b As Integer, startPosition As String)
        ' Parse starting position
        Dim colStart As Integer = Asc(startPosition(0)) - Asc("a"c) ' 0-based column
        Dim rowStart As Integer = Integer.Parse(startPosition.Substring(1)) ' 1-based row

        ' Generate all possible delta (dx, dy) combinations
        Dim deltas As New HashSet(Of Tuple(Of Integer, Integer))
        For Each deltaPart In {Tuple.Create(a, b), Tuple.Create(b, a)}
            For Each sx In {1, -1}
                For Each sy In {1, -1}
                    Dim dx As Integer = deltaPart.Item1 * sx
                    Dim dy As Integer = deltaPart.Item2 * sy
                    deltas.Add(Tuple.Create(dx, dy))
                Next
            Next
        Next

        ' Calculate valid moves
        Dim validMoves As New List(Of String)
        For Each delta In deltas
            Dim newRow As Integer = rowStart + delta.Item1
            Dim newCol As Integer = colStart + delta.Item2

            ' Check if the new position is within bounds
            If newRow >= 1 AndAlso newRow <= 8 AndAlso newCol >= 0 AndAlso newCol < 8 Then
                Dim colChar As Char = Chr(newCol + Asc("a"c))
                validMoves.Add($"{colChar}{newRow}")
            End If
        Next

        ' Sort moves lexicographically
        validMoves.Sort()

        ' Output results
        Console.WriteLine(validMoves.Count)
        If validMoves.Count > 0 Then
            Console.WriteLine(String.Join(" ", validMoves))
        Else
            Console.WriteLine()
        End If
    End Sub
End Module

            Dim newRow As Integer = rowStart + delta.Item1
            Dim newCol As Integer = colStart + delta.Item2

            ' Check if the new position is within bounds
            If newRow >= 1 AndAlso newRow <= 8 AndAlso newCol >= 0 AndAlso newCol < 8 Then
                Dim colChar As Char = Chr(newCol + Asc("a"c))
                validMoves.Add($"{colChar}{newRow}")
            End If
        Next

        ' Sort moves lexicographically
        validMoves.Sort()

        ' Output results
        Console.WriteLine(validMoves.Count)
        If validMoves.Count > 0 Then
            Console.WriteLine(String.Join(" ", validMoves))
        Else
            Console.WriteLine()
        End If
    End Sub

Module SumExceptSelf
    ' Computes a new array where each element at index i is the sum of all elements
    ' in the original array except the element at index i.
    ' 
    ' Args:
    ' - nums: An array of integers.
    '
    ' Returns:
    ' - An array of integers where each element is the sum of all other elements.
    Function SumExceptSelf(nums As Integer()) As Integer()
        If nums Is Nothing OrElse nums.Length = 0 Then
            Return New Integer() {}
        End If

        Dim totalSum As Integer = 0
        For Each num As Integer In nums
            totalSum += num
        Next

        Dim result(nums.Length - 1) As Integer
        For i As Integer = 0 To nums.Length - 1
            result(i) = totalSum - nums(i)
        Next

        Return result
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module SafeSquaresCounter
    ' Counts the number of safe d x d squares in a grid where no obstacles are present.
    ' The grid is represented as a 2D array where 1 indicates an obstacle and 0 indicates a safe cell.
    ' The function iterates over all possible square sizes from 1 to the minimum of grid rows and columns.
    ' For each square size, it checks all possible positions in the grid to see if they are obstacle-free.
    Function CountSafeSquares(grid As Integer(,), R As Integer, C As Integer) As Integer
        Dim res As Integer = 0
        Dim maxD As Integer = Math.Min(R, C)
        
        For d As Integer = 1 To maxD
            Dim numRows As Integer = R - d + 1
            Dim numCols As Integer = C - d + 1
            
            If numRows <= 0 OrElse numCols <= 0 Then
                Continue For
            End If
            
            For i As Integer = 0 To numRows - 1
                For j As Integer = 0 To numCols - 1
                    Dim valid As Boolean = True
                    
                    For x As Integer = i To i + d - 1
                        If Not valid Then
                            Exit For
                        End If
                        
                        For y As Integer = j To j + d - 1
                            If grid(x, y) = 1 Then
                                valid = False
                                Exit For
                            End If
                        Next
                    Next
                    
                    If valid Then
                        res += 1
                    End If
                Next
            Next
        Next
        
        Return res
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module DateValidator
    ' Checks if a given year is a leap year.
    ' A year is a leap year if:
    ' - It is divisible by 400, or
    ' - It is divisible by 4 but not by 100.
    Function IsLeapYear(year As Integer) As Boolean
        If year Mod 400 = 0 Then
            Return True
        ElseIf year Mod 100 = 0 Then
            Return False
        ElseIf year Mod 4 = 0 Then
            Return True
        Else
            Return False
        End If
    End Function

    ' Validates a given date (day, month, year).
    ' Returns "Valid" if the date is valid, otherwise "Invalid".
    Function ValidateDate(day As Integer, month As Integer, year As Integer) As String
        If month < 1 OrElse month > 12 Then
            Return "Invalid"
        End If

        If day < 1 Then
            Return "Invalid"
        End If

        Dim maxDay As Integer

        Select Case month
            Case 2
                maxDay = If(IsLeapYear(year), 29, 28)
            Case 4, 6, 9, 11
                maxDay = 30
            Case Else
                maxDay = 31
        End Select

        If day > maxDay Then
            Return "Invalid"
        Else
            Return "Valid"
        End If
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module TreeLeafPairing
    ' This program finds all leaves in a tree (nodes with degree 1) and pairs them
    ' The goal is to pair leaves such that each leaf is in at most one pair
    ' and the number of pairs is (number of leaves + 1) // 2
    
    ' Finds all leaves in an adjacency list and returns them as a list
    Function FindLeaves(adj As List(Of List(Of Integer))) As List(Of Integer)
        Dim leaves As New List(Of Integer)()
        For i As Integer = 1 To adj.Count - 1
            If adj(i).Count = 1 Then
                leaves.Add(i)
            End If
        Next
        Return leaves
    End Function
    
    ' Pairs leaves by matching first half with second half and prints the pairs
    Sub PairAndPrintLeaves(leaves As List(Of Integer))
        Dim k As Integer = leaves.Count
        Dim m As Integer = (k + 1) \ 2
        Console.WriteLine(m)
        
        For i As Integer = 0 To m - 1
            Console.WriteLine("{0} {1}", leaves(i), leaves(i + (k \ 2)))
        Next
    End Sub
End Module

Imports System
Imports System.Linq

Module LongestCommonPrefix
    ' Finds the longest common prefix among an array of strings.
    ' Returns an empty string if the input array is empty.
    Function LongestCommonPrefix(strings As String()) As String
        If strings Is Nothing OrElse strings.Length = 0 Then
            Return ""
        End If
        
        ' The minimum length string will define the maximum possible length of the common prefix
        Dim minLength As Integer = strings.Min(Function(s) s.Length)
        
        ' Find the longest common prefix
        For i As Integer = 0 To minLength - 1
            ' Check if the current character is the same in all strings
            Dim currentChar As Char = strings(0)(i)
            If Not strings.All(Function(s) s(i) = currentChar) Then
                Return strings(0).Substring(0, i) ' Return the common prefix up to current index
            End If
        Next
        
        Return strings(0).Substring(0, minLength) ' All characters were the same up to the minimum string length
    End Function

    ' Processes test cases and returns the longest common prefix for each case.
    ' Each test case is a tuple where the first element is an integer (ignored here) and the second is an array of employee tuples (id, string).
    Function ProcessTestCases(testCases As List(Of Tuple(Of Integer, List(Of Tuple(Of Integer, String))))) As List(Of String)
        Dim results As New List(Of String)
        
        For Each testCase In testCases
            Dim employees = testCase.Item2
            Dim strings As String() = employees.Select(Function(emp) emp.Item2).ToArray()
            results.Add(LongestCommonPrefix(strings))
        Next
        
        Return results
    End Function
End Module

Module GeometricSequenceChecker
    ' Determines whether a sequence of numbers is geometric.
    ' A sequence is geometric if each term after the first is the product of the previous term and a constant "common ratio".
    ' Returns True if the sequence is geometric, otherwise False.
    Function IsGeometricSequence(seq As Double()) As Boolean
        If seq Is Nothing OrElse seq.Length <= 1 Then
            Return True
        End If

        ' Handle the case where the first term is zero
        If seq(0) = 0 Then
            For Each num As Double In seq
                If num <> 0 Then
                    Return False
                End If
            Next
            Return True
        End If

        Dim commonRatio As Double = seq(1) / seq(0)

        For i As Integer = 1 To seq.Length - 1
            If seq(i) <> seq(i - 1) * commonRatio Then
                Return False
            End If
        Next

        Return True
    End Function
End Module

Module MaxSubsequenceSum
    ' Computes the maximum possible sum of a non-empty subsequence.
    ' If all numbers are negative, returns the maximum number.
    ' Otherwise, returns the sum of all positive numbers in the list.
    Function MaxSubsequenceSum(nums As Integer()) As Integer
        Dim allNegative As Boolean = True
        
        ' Check if all numbers are negative
        For Each num As Integer In nums
            If num >= 0 Then
                allNegative = False
                Exit For
            End If
        Next
        
        ' If all numbers are negative, return the maximum number
        If allNegative Then
            Return nums.Max()
        End If
        
        ' Sum all positive numbers in the list
        Dim totalSum As Integer = 0
        For Each num As Integer In nums
            If num > 0 Then
                totalSum += num
            End If
        Next
        
        Return totalSum
    End Function
End Module

Module PatternMatcher
    ' Counts the number of times a smaller grid (rig) appears in a larger grid (map)
    Function CountPatternMatches(rig As String(), mapData As String()) As Integer
        Dim count As Integer = 0
        Dim Li As Integer = rig.Length
        If Li = 0 Then Return 0
        Dim Ci As Integer = rig(0).Length
        Dim Lm As Integer = mapData.Length
        If Lm = 0 Then Return 0
        Dim Cm As Integer = mapData(0).Length
        
        ' Iterate over all possible starting positions in the map
        For i As Integer = 0 To Lm - Li
            For j As Integer = 0 To Cm - Ci
                Dim match As Boolean = True
                
                ' Check each cell in the rig pattern
                For x As Integer = 0 To Li - 1
                    For y As Integer = 0 To Ci - 1
                        If rig(x)(y) <> mapData(i + x)(j + y) Then
                            match = False
                            Exit For
                        End If
                    Next
                    If Not match Then Exit For
                Next
                
                If match Then count += 1
            Next
        Next
        
        Return count
    End Function
End Module

Module FixFreeChecker
    ' Checks if a set of three words is fix-free (neither a prefix nor suffix of each other)
    ' Returns True if the words are fix-free, False otherwise
    Function IsFixFree(words As String()) As Boolean
        For i As Integer = 0 To 2
            For j As Integer = 0 To 2
                If i = j Then Continue For
                
                Dim x As String = words(i)
                Dim y As String = words(j)
                
                ' Check prefix condition
                If x.Length <= y.Length AndAlso y.StartsWith(x) Then
                    Return False
                End If
                
                ' Check suffix condition
                If x.Length <= y.Length AndAlso y.EndsWith(x) Then
                    Return False
                End If
            Next
        Next
        Return True
    End Function

    ' Processes multiple test cases of three words each and checks if they're fix-free
    Sub ProcessTestCases(testCases As List(Of String()))
        For Each testCase As String() In testCases
            Console.Write("Input: ")
            Console.WriteLine(String.Join(", ", testCase))
            
            Dim result As Boolean = IsFixFree(testCase)
            Console.WriteLine($"Fix-Free: {If(result, "Yes", "No")}")
            Console.WriteLine()
        Next
    End Sub
End Module

Imports System

Module RoomVisiting
    ' Determines if all rooms can be visited starting from room 0.
    ' Rooms are represented as a list of lists, where each sublist contains keys to other rooms.
    ' Uses depth-first search (DFS) to traverse through the rooms.
    Function CanVisitAllRooms(rooms As List(Of List(Of Integer))) As Boolean
        Dim visited As Boolean() = New Boolean(rooms.Count - 1) {}
        visited(0) = True
        Dim stack As Stack(Of Integer) = New Stack(Of Integer)()
        stack.Push(0)
        
        While stack.Count > 0
            Dim curRoom As Integer = stack.Pop()
            For Each room As Integer In rooms(curRoom)
                If Not visited(room) Then
                    visited(room) = True
                    stack.Push(room)
                End If
            Next
        End While
        
        Return Array.TrueForAll(visited, Function(v) v)
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module PartitionCalculator
    ' Computes the number of ways to represent m as a sum of numbers up to n
    ' using dynamic programming approach
    Function CountPartitions(m As Integer, n As Integer) As Integer
        ' Create a DP table of size (m+1) x (n+1)
        Dim dp(m, n) As Integer
        
        ' Base case: there's one way to represent 0 with any numbers (using no numbers)
        For j As Integer = 0 To n
            dp(0, j) = 1
        Next
        
        For i As Integer = 1 To m
            For j As Integer = 1 To n
                If j > i Then
                    dp(i, j) = dp(i, i)
                Else
                    dp(i, j) = dp(i - j, j) + dp(i, j - 1)
                End If
            Next
        Next
        
        Return dp(m, n)
    End Function
End Module

    Function CountPartitions(m As Integer, n As Integer) As Integer
        ' Create a DP table of size (m+1) x (n+1)
        Dim dp(m, n) As Integer
        
        ' Base case: there's one way to represent 0 with any numbers (using no numbers)
        For j As Integer = 0 To n
            dp(0, j) = 1
        Next
        
        For i As Integer = 1 To m
            For j As Integer = 1 To n
                If j > i Then
                    dp(i, j) = dp(i, i)
                Else
                    dp(i, j) = dp(i - j, j) + dp(i, j - 1)
                End If
            Next
        Next
        
        Return dp(m, n)
    End Function
End Module

Module PartitionCalculatorTests
    Sub Main()
        Debug.Assert(PartitionCalculator.CountPartitions(5, 3) = 5)
        Debug.Assert(PartitionCalculator.CountPartitions(4, 4) = 5)
        Debug.Assert(PartitionCalculator.CountPartitions(7, 2) = 4)
        Debug.Assert(PartitionCalculator.CountPartitions(0, 5) = 1)
        Debug.Assert(PartitionCalculator.CountPartitions(10, 10) = 42)
    End Sub
End Module

Module GreatestEvenDivisor
    ' Precomputes the greatest even divisors and their prefix sums up to maxNum
    ' Returns an array where each element at index i contains the sum of greatest even divisors from 1 to i
    Function Precompute(maxNum As Integer) As Long()
        ' Initialize array to store greatest even divisors
        Dim ged(maxNum) As Long
        For x As Integer = 1 To maxNum
            If x Mod 2 = 0 Then
                ged(x) = x
            Else
                ged(x) = 0
            End If
        Next
        
        ' Compute prefix sums
        Dim prefix(maxNum) As Long
        For i As Integer = 1 To maxNum
            prefix(i) = prefix(i - 1) + ged(i)
        Next
        
        Return prefix
    End Function
    
    ' Calculates the sum of greatest even divisors between l and r (inclusive)
    ' using the precomputed prefix sums
    Function QuerySum(l As Integer, r As Integer, prefix As Long()) As Long
        Return prefix(r) - prefix(l - 1)
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module EvenDigitProduct
    ' Computes the product of all even digits in the given number N.
    ' If there are no even digits, returns 1.
    Function EvenProduct(N As Integer) As Integer
        Dim product As Integer = 1
        Dim hasEvenDigit As Boolean = False
        
        ' Convert the number to a string to iterate over each digit
        For Each c As Char In N.ToString()
            Dim digit As Integer = Integer.Parse(c.ToString())
            ' Check if the digit is even
            If digit Mod 2 = 0 Then
                product *= digit
                hasEvenDigit = True
            End If
        Next
        
        ' Return the product if there were even digits, otherwise return 1
        Return If(hasEvenDigit, product, 1)
    End Function
End Module

Imports System
Imports System.Collections.Generic

Module SchedulerModule
    ' Represents a scheduler that manages tasks with start and end times.
    ' Provides functionality to add, remove, and find the maximum number of non-overlapping tasks.
    Public Class Scheduler
        Private tasks As List(Of Tuple(Of Integer, Integer))
        
        ' Initializes a new instance of the Scheduler class.
        Public Sub New()
            tasks = New List(Of Tuple(Of Integer, Integer))()
        End Sub
        
        ' Adds a task to the scheduler if it doesn't already exist.
        Public Sub AddTask(start As Integer, [end] As Integer)
            Dim newTask As Tuple(Of Integer, Integer) = Tuple.Create(start, [end])
            If Not tasks.Contains(newTask) Then
                tasks.Add(newTask)
            End If
        End Sub
        
        ' Removes a task from the scheduler if it exists.
        Public Sub RemoveTask(start As Integer, [end] As Integer)
            Dim taskToRemove As Tuple(Of Integer, Integer) = Tuple.Create(start, [end])
            If tasks.Contains(taskToRemove) Then
                tasks.Remove(taskToRemove)
            End If
        End Sub
        
        ' Returns the maximum number of non-overlapping tasks.
        Public Function MaxNonOverlappingTasks() As Integer
            If tasks.Count = 0 Then
                Return 0
            End If
            
            ' Sort tasks by their end time
            Dim sortedTasks As List(Of Tuple(Of Integer, Integer)) = New List(Of Tuple(Of Integer, Integer))(tasks)
            sortedTasks.Sort(Function(x, y) x.Item2.CompareTo(y.Item2))
            
            Dim count As Integer = 0
            Dim lastEndTime As Integer = Integer.MinValue
            
            For Each task In sortedTasks
                If task.Item1 >= lastEndTime Then
                    count += 1
                    lastEndTime = task.Item2
                End If
            Next
            
            Return count
        End Function
    End Class
End Module

Module PlantWateringCalculator
    ' Determines the minimum number of days required to water all plants
    ' so that all of them achieve the height of the tallest plant.
    '
    ' Parameters:
    ' plantHeights - An array of integers representing the heights of the plants.
    '
    ' Returns:
    ' Integer - The minimum number of days required.
    Function MinDaysToEqualHeight(plantHeights As Integer()) As Integer
        If plantHeights Is Nothing OrElse plantHeights.Length = 0 Then
            Return 0
        End If
        
        Dim maxHeight As Integer = plantHeights.Max()
        Dim totalDays As Integer = plantHeights.Sum(Function(height) maxHeight - height)
        
        Return totalDays
    End Function

Imports System

Module WordAndNumberCounter
    ' Takes a string containing a mix of words and numbers, separated by spaces,
    ' and returns a dictionary with the counts of words and numeric values.
    '
    ' Args:
    ' inputString (String): The input string containing words and numbers.
    '
    ' Returns:
    ' Dictionary(Of String, Integer): A dictionary with two keys: "words" and "numbers" indicating the counts.
    Function CountWordsAndNumbers(inputString As String) As Dictionary(Of String, Integer)
        Dim wordsCount As Integer = 0
        Dim numbersCount As Integer = 0
        
        Dim elements As String() = inputString.Split(New Char() {" "c}, StringSplitOptions.RemoveEmptyEntries)
        
        For Each element As String In elements
            Dim isNumber As Boolean
            Dim numericValue As Double
            isNumber = Double.TryParse(element, numericValue)
            
            If isNumber Then
                numbersCount += 1
            ElseIf element.All(AddressOf Char.IsLetter) Then
                wordsCount += 1
            End If
        Next
        
        Dim result As New Dictionary(Of String, Integer)
        result.Add("words", wordsCount)
        result.Add("numbers", numbersCount)
        
        Return result
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module EventOverlapChecker
    ' Determines if any event windows overlap in the given list of events.
    ' Each event is represented as a Tuple of (start, end).
    ' Returns "YES" if any event windows overlap, otherwise "NO".
    Function HasEventOverlap(events As Tuple(Of Integer, Integer)()) As String
        ' Sort events by start time
        Array.Sort(events, Function(x, y) x.Item1.CompareTo(y.Item1))
        
        ' Iterate over the events and check for overlap
        Dim previousEnd As Integer = -1
        For Each eventItem In events
            Dim start As Integer = eventItem.Item1
            Dim [end] As Integer = eventItem.Item2
            
            If start < previousEnd Then
                Return "YES"
            End If
            previousEnd = [end]
        Next
        
        Return "NO"
    End Function
End Module

    Function MinInSlidingWindow(nums As Integer(), k As Integer) As List(Of Integer)
        Dim result As New List(Of Integer)()

        If nums Is Nothing OrElse nums.Length = 0 OrElse k = 0 Then

        End If

        Dim dq As New LinkedList(Of Integer)() ' Stores indices of nums, elements are in non-decreasing order
        
        For i As Integer = 0 To n - 1
            ' Remove indices that are out of the current window
            If dq.Count > 0 AndAlso dq.First.Value = i - k Then

            End If

            While dq.Count > 0 AndAlso nums(dq.Last.Value) > nums(i)

Imports System

Module StringModifier
    ' Modifies a string based on the sum of digits in the input string.
    ' If there are digits, computes their sum and repeats the string that many times.
    ' If there are no digits, returns "Nothing!".
    Function ModifyString(s As String) As String
        Dim digitSum As Integer = 0
        
        ' Calculate the sum of all digits in the string
        For Each c As Char In s
            If Char.IsDigit(c) Then
                digitSum += Integer.Parse(c.ToString())
            End If
        Next
        
        ' Return the appropriate result based on the digit sum
        If digitSum = 0 Then
            Return "Nothing!"
        Else
            Return String.Concat(Enumerable.Repeat(s, digitSum))
        End If
    End Function
End Module

Imports System
Imports System.Collections.Generic

Module ExponentCalculator
    ' Processes an array of numbers to find the highest exponent after merging pairs.
    ' The merging process combines pairs of numbers with the same exponent to form numbers with exponent + 1.
    ' Returns 2 raised to the highest exponent found, or 0 if no numbers are present.
    Function CalculateHighestExponent(numbers As Integer()) As Integer
        Dim counts As New Dictionary(Of Integer, Integer)()
        
        ' Calculate initial exponents for each number and count occurrences
        For Each num As Integer In numbers
            Dim exp As Integer = 0
            If num <> 0 Then
                Dim tmp As Integer = num
                While tmp > 1
                    tmp >>= 1
                    exp += 1
                End While
            End If
            
            If counts.ContainsKey(exp) Then
                counts(exp) += 1
            Else
                counts(exp) = 1
            End If
        Next
        
        Dim currentMaxExp As Integer = If(counts.Count > 0, counts.Keys.Max(), 0)
        
        ' Process exponents to merge pairs
        For x As Integer = 0 To currentMaxExp + 2000
            If counts.ContainsKey(x) Then
                Dim pairs As Integer = counts(x) \ 2
                If pairs > 0 Then
                    If counts.ContainsKey(x + 1) Then
                        counts(x + 1) += pairs
                    Else
                        counts(x + 1) = pairs
                    End If
                    counts(x) -= pairs * 2
                    
                    If x + 1 > currentMaxExp Then
                        currentMaxExp = x + 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        Next
        
        ' Find the highest exponent with at least one occurrence
        Dim resultExp As Integer = currentMaxExp
        While resultExp >= 0 AndAlso (Not counts.ContainsKey(resultExp) OrElse counts(resultExp) = 0)
            resultExp -= 1
        End While
        
        Return If(resultExp >= 0, CInt(Math.Pow(2, resultExp)), 0)
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module GridPathMaxFun
    ' Returns the maximum fun level Johnny can achieve while moving from the top-left to bottom-right of the grid.
    ' Uses dynamic programming to calculate the maximum path sum.
    ' 
    ' Parameters:
    '   n - Integer: the size of the grid
    '   grid - Integer()(): the n x n grid with non-negative integers representing the fun level of each cell
    ' Returns:
    '   Integer: the maximum fun level Johnny can achieve
    Function MaxFunLevel(n As Integer, grid As Integer()()) As Integer
        ' Create a 2D dp array to store the maximum fun level at each cell
        Dim dp(n - 1, n - 1) As Integer
        
        ' Set the initial position
        dp(0, 0) = grid(0)(0)
        
        ' Fill the first row
        For j As Integer = 1 To n - 1
            dp(0, j) = dp(0, j - 1) + grid(0)(j)
        Next
        
        ' Fill the first column
        For i As Integer = 1 To n - 1
            dp(i, 0) = dp(i - 1, 0) + grid(i)(0)
        Next
        
        ' Fill the rest of the dp table
        For i As Integer = 1 To n - 1
            For j As Integer = 1 To n - 1
                dp(i, j) = Math.Max(dp(i - 1, j), dp(i, j - 1)) + grid(i)(j)
            Next
        Next
        
        ' The answer is the maximum fun level at the bottom-right cell
        Return dp(n - 1, n - 1)
    End Function
End Module

Imports System
Imports System.Diagnostics

Module GridPathMaxFun
    ' Returns the maximum fun level Johnny can achieve while moving from the top-left to bottom-right of the grid.
    ' Uses dynamic programming to calculate the maximum path sum.
    ' 
    ' Parameters:
    '   n - Integer: the size of the grid
    '   grid - Integer()(): the n x n grid with non-negative integers representing the fun level of each cell
    ' Returns:
    '   Integer: the maximum fun level Johnny can achieve
    Function MaxFunLevel(n As Integer, grid As Integer()()) As Integer
        ' Create a 2D dp array to store the maximum fun level at each cell
        Dim dp(n - 1, n - 1) As Integer
        
        ' Set the initial position
        dp(0, 0) = grid(0)(0)
        
        ' Fill the first row
        For j As Integer = 1 To n - 1
            dp(0, j) = dp(0, j - 1) + grid(0)(j)
        Next
        
        ' Fill the first column
        For i As Integer = 1 To n - 1
            dp(i, 0) = dp(i - 1, 0) + grid(i)(0)
        Next
        
        ' Fill the rest of the dp table
        For i As Integer = 1 To n - 1
            For j As Integer = 1 To n - 1
                dp(i, j) = Math.Max(dp(i - 1, j), dp(i, j - 1)) + grid(i)(j)
            Next
        Next
        
        ' The answer is the maximum fun level at the bottom-right cell
        Return dp(n - 1, n - 1)
    End Function
End Module

Module GridPathMaxFunTests
    Sub Main()
        ' Test Case 1: Simple 2x2 grid
        Dim grid1 As Integer()() = {
            New Integer() {1, 2},
            New Integer() {3, 4}
        }

        ' Test Case 2: 3x3 grid with equal values
        Dim grid2 As Integer()() = {
            New Integer() {5, 5, 5},
            New Integer() {5, 5, 5},
            New Integer() {5, 5, 5}
        }
        Debug.Assert(MaxFunLevel(3, grid2) = 25)

            New Integer() {1, 3, 1},
            New Integer() {1, 5, 1},
            New Integer() {4, 2, 1}

Imports System
Imports System.Collections.Generic

Module TopologicalSort
    ' Finds a topological ordering of items based on dependencies
    ' Returns a list representing the valid ordering or a message if no valid ordering exists
    Function FindOrdering(items As List(Of String), dependencies As List(Of Tuple(Of String, String))) As Object
        ' Create a graph and a dictionary to store in-degrees
        Dim graph As New Dictionary(Of String, List(Of String))
        Dim inDegree As New Dictionary(Of String, Integer)
        
        ' Initialize graph and in-degree for all items
        For Each item As String In items
            graph(item) = New List(Of String)
            inDegree(item) = 0
        Next
        
        ' Build the graph and fill in-degrees
        For Each dependency As Tuple(Of String, String) In dependencies
            Dim itemB As String = dependency.Item1
            Dim itemA As String = dependency.Item2
            
            graph(itemB).Add(itemA)
            inDegree(itemA) += 1
        Next
        
        ' Use a queue to store items with in-degree 0
        Dim zeroInDegree As New Queue(Of String)
        For Each item In items
            If inDegree(item) = 0 Then
                zeroInDegree.Enqueue(item)
            End If
        Next
        
        Dim sortOrder As New List(Of String)
        
        ' Process nodes with in-degree 0
        While zeroInDegree.Count > 0
            Dim current As String = zeroInDegree.Dequeue()
            sortOrder.Add(current)
            
            For Each neighbor As String In graph(current)
                inDegree(neighbor) -= 1
                If inDegree(neighbor) = 0 Then
                    zeroInDegree.Enqueue(neighbor)
                End If
            Next
        End While
        
        ' Check if a valid ordering was found
        If sortOrder.Count = items.Count Then
            Return sortOrder
        Else
            Return "No valid ordering possible"
        End If
    End Function
End Module

Imports System
Imports System.Linq

Module ProblemAnalyzer
    ' Analyzes problem ratings to find problems that are simplest (minimum in a row) 
    ' for more than half of the participants and not hardest (maximum) in any row.
    ' Returns a list of problem indices (1-based) that meet the criteria.
    Function AnalyzeProblems(n As Integer, p As Integer, ratings As Integer()()) As List(Of Integer)
        Dim result As New List(Of Integer)

        For problem As Integer = 0 To p - 1
            Dim simplestCount As Integer = 0
            Dim isHardest As Boolean = False

            For Each row As Integer() In ratings
                Dim currentVal As Integer = row(problem)
                ' Check if current problem is the simplest in this row
                If currentVal = row.Min() Then
                    simplestCount += 1
                End If
                ' Check if current problem is the hardest in this row
                If currentVal = row.Max() Then
                    isHardest = True
                End If
            Next

            ' Add to result if more than half found it simplest and never hardest
            If simplestCount > n \ 2 AndAlso Not isHardest Then
                result.Add(problem + 1) ' Convert to 1-based index
            End If
        Next

        Return result
    End Function

    ' Formats the result for output according to requirements
    Function FormatResult(result As List(Of Integer)) As String
        If result.Count = 0 Then
            Return "0"
        Else
            Return String.Join(" ", result.OrderBy(Function(x) x))
        End If
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module KMPPrefixAnalysis
    ' Computes the prefix function (KMP's pi array) for a given string
    Function ComputePrefixFunction(s As String) As Integer()
        Dim n As Integer = s.Length
        Dim pi(n - 1) As Integer
        
        For i As Integer = 1 To n - 1
            Dim j As Integer = pi(i - 1)
            
            While j > 0 AndAlso s(i) <> s(j)
                j = pi(j - 1)
            End While
            
            If s(i) = s(j) Then
                j += 1
            End If
            
            pi(i) = j
        Next
        
        Return pi
    End Function

    ' Computes the maximum length of repeated prefix substrings
    Function ComputeMaxPrefixLength(s As String) As Integer
        If String.IsNullOrEmpty(s) Then
            Return 0
        End If
        
        Dim n As Integer = s.Length
        Dim pi As Integer() = ComputePrefixFunction(s)
        Dim cnt(n - 1) As Integer
        Dim maxLen As Integer = 1
        
        cnt(0) = 1
        
        For i As Integer = 1 To n - 1
            If pi(i) = 0 Then
                cnt(i) = 1
            Else
                cnt(i) = cnt(pi(i) - 1) + 1
            End If
            
            If cnt(i) > maxLen Then
                maxLen = cnt(i)
            End If
        Next
        
        Return maxLen
    End Function
End Module

Imports System
Imports System.Collections.Generic

Module LongestSubarrayWithKDistinct
    ' Finds the longest subarray with at most K distinct elements.
    ' Returns the start and end indices (1-based) of the longest subarray.
    Function FindLongestSubarray(arr As Integer(), k As Integer) As Tuple(Of Integer, Integer)
        Dim freq As New Dictionary(Of Integer, Integer)()
        Dim currentDistinct As Integer = 0
        Dim maxLen As Integer = 0
        Dim start As Integer = 0
        Dim left As Integer = 0

        For right As Integer = 0 To arr.Length - 1
            Dim x As Integer = arr(right)
            
            ' Update frequency dictionary
            If freq.ContainsKey(x) Then
                freq(x) += 1
            Else
                freq(x) = 1
                currentDistinct += 1
            End If

            ' If current distinct exceeds k, move left pointer to the right
            While currentDistinct > k
                Dim leftX As Integer = arr(left)
                freq(leftX) -= 1
                If freq(leftX) = 0 Then
                    freq.Remove(leftX)
                    currentDistinct -= 1
                End If
                left += 1
            End While

            ' Update the maximum length and indices if current window is larger
            Dim currentLength As Integer = right - left + 1
            If currentLength > maxLen Then
                maxLen = currentLength
                start = left
            End If
        Next

        ' Return 1-based indices
        Return New Tuple(Of Integer, Integer)(start + 1, start + maxLen)
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module ZeroCountInProduct
    ' Counts the number of times a prime number p appears in the factorization of numbers in the range [start, end]
    Function CountPrimeInRange(start As Integer, [end] As Integer, p As Integer) As Integer
        If start > [end] Then
            Return 0
        End If
        
        Dim count As Integer = 0
        Dim current As Long = p
        
        While current <= [end]
            ' Calculate how many multiples of current are in the range
            Dim cnt As Integer = ([end] \ current) - ((start - 1) \ current)
            count += cnt
            current *= p
        End While
        
        Return count
    End Function

    ' Calculates the number of trailing zeros in the product of numbers in the range [a, b]
    Function CalculateTrailingZeros(a As Integer, b As Integer) As Integer
        ' Check if the interval includes zero
        If a <= 0 AndAlso b >= 0 Then
            Return 1
        End If
        
        Dim l, r As Integer
        
        ' Determine the actual range to consider
        If a > 0 AndAlso b > 0 Then
            l = a
            r = b
        ElseIf a < 0 AndAlso b < 0 Then
            l = -b
            r = -a
        Else
            ' This case should not happen since zero case is already checked
            l = 0
            r = 0
        End If
        
        ' Count the number of 2s and 5s in the factorizations of numbers in the range
        Dim sum2 As Integer = CountPrimeInRange(l, r, 2)
        Dim sum5 As Integer = CountPrimeInRange(l, r, 5)
        
        ' The number of trailing zeros is the minimum of sum2 and sum5
        Return Math.Min(sum2, sum5)
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module PolygonAreaCalculator
    ' Computes the area and direction (CW or CCW) of a polygon given its vertices.
    ' The vertices are provided as an array of tuples (x, y).
    ' The direction is determined by the sign of the cross product sum.
    ' The area is computed using the shoelace formula.
    Function ComputePolygonAreaAndDirection(vertices As Tuple(Of Integer, Integer)()) As Tuple(Of String, Double)
        Dim sumS As Double = 0
        Dim n As Integer = vertices.Length
        
        For i As Integer = 0 To n - 1
            Dim xi As Integer = vertices(i).Item1
            Dim yi As Integer = vertices(i).Item2
            Dim xn As Integer = vertices((i + 1) Mod n).Item1
            Dim yn As Integer = vertices((i + 1) Mod n).Item2
            sumS += xi * yn - xn * yi
        Next
        
        Dim area As Double = Math.Abs(sumS) / 2.0
        Dim direction As String = If(sumS > 0, "CCW", "CW")
        
        Return New Tuple(Of String, Double)(direction, area)
    End Function
End Module

Imports System
Imports System.Linq

Module StringAndSumChecker
    ' Checks if the sum of ASCII values of characters in the string matches
    ' the sum of numbers in the list. Further checks if the string contains at least
    ' 3 unique vowels and starts with a capital letter.
    '
    ' Args:
    '   inputString (String): The string to check.
    '   numbers (Integer()): The list of numbers.
    '   target (Integer): The target number to return.
    '
    ' Returns:
    '   Integer?: The target number if conditions are met, otherwise Nothing.
    Function CheckStringAndSum(inputString As String, numbers As Integer(), target As Integer) As Integer?
        ' Check if the string starts with a capital letter
        If String.IsNullOrEmpty(inputString) OrElse Not Char.IsUpper(inputString(0)) Then
            Return Nothing
        End If

        ' Calculate the sum of ASCII values in the string
        Dim asciiSum As Integer = inputString.Sum(Function(c) Asc(c))

        ' Calculate the sum of numbers in the list
        Dim listSum As Integer = numbers.Sum()

        ' Check if sums match
        If asciiSum <> listSum Then
            Return Nothing
        End If

        ' Check if the string contains at least 3 unique vowels
        Dim vowels As String = "AEIOUaeiou"
        Dim uniqueVowels As Integer = inputString.Where(Function(c) vowels.Contains(c)).Distinct().Count()

        If uniqueVowels < 3 Then
            Return Nothing
        End If

        Return target
    End Function
End Module

Imports System
Imports System.Diagnostics
Imports System.Linq

Module StringAndSumChecker
    ' Checks if the sum of ASCII values of characters in the string matches
    ' the sum of numbers in the list. Further checks if the string contains at least
    ' 3 unique vowels and starts with a capital letter.
    '
    ' Args:
    '   inputString (String): The string to check.
    '   numbers (Integer()): The list of numbers.
    '   target (Integer): The target number to return.
    '
    ' Returns:
    '   Integer?: The target number if conditions are met, otherwise Nothing.
    Function CheckStringAndSum(inputString As String, numbers As Integer(), target As Integer) As Integer?
        ' Check if the string starts with a capital letter
        If String.IsNullOrEmpty(inputString) OrElse Not Char.IsUpper(inputString(0)) Then
            Return Nothing
        End If

        ' Calculate the sum of ASCII values in the string
        Dim asciiSum As Integer = inputString.Sum(Function(c) Asc(c))

        ' Calculate the sum of numbers in the list
        Dim listSum As Integer = numbers.Sum()

        ' Check if sums match
        If asciiSum <> listSum Then
            Return Nothing
        End If

        ' Check if the string contains at least 3 unique vowels
        Dim vowels As String = "AEIOUaeiou"
        Dim uniqueVowels As Integer = inputString.Where(Function(c) vowels.Contains(c)).Distinct().Count()

        If uniqueVowels < 3 Then
            Return Nothing
        End If

        Return target
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module PrimeSetBitsCounter
    ' Returns True if n is a prime number, else False.
    Function IsPrime(n As Integer) As Boolean
        If n <= 1 Then
            Return False
        End If
        If n <= 3 Then
            Return True
        End If
        If n Mod 2 = 0 Or n Mod 3 = 0 Then
            Return False
        End If
        
        Dim i As Integer = 5
        While i * i <= n
            If n Mod i = 0 Or n Mod (i + 2) = 0 Then
                Return False
            End If
            i += 6
        End While
        
        Return True
    End Function

    ' Counts how many numbers between start and end inclusive have a prime number of set bits in binary representation.
    Function CountPrimeSetBits(start As Integer, endVal As Integer) As Integer
        Dim primeCount As Integer = 0
        
        For num As Integer = start To endVal
            Dim binaryString As String = Convert.ToString(num, 2)
            Dim setBits As Integer = binaryString.Count(Function(c) c = "1"c)
            
            If IsPrime(setBits) Then
                primeCount += 1
            End If
        Next
        
        Return primeCount
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module BookReader
    ' Computes the maximum number of books that can be read without exceeding the page limit L.
    ' Uses a sliding window approach to efficiently find the solution.
    Function MaxBooksRead(N As Integer, L As Integer, pages As Integer()) As Integer
        Dim start As Integer = 0
        Dim totalPages As Integer = 0
        Dim maxBooks As Integer = 0
        
        For endIdx As Integer = 0 To N - 1
            totalPages += pages(endIdx)
            
            ' Adjust the window by moving the start pointer if the total pages exceed L
            While totalPages > L
                totalPages -= pages(start)
                start += 1
            End While
            
            ' Update the maximum number of books that can be read
            maxBooks = Math.Max(maxBooks, endIdx - start + 1)
        Next
        
        Return maxBooks
    End Function

    ' Processes a list of test cases and returns the results for each case.
    Function ProcessTestCases(testCases As Object()) As Integer()
        Dim results As New System.Collections.Generic.List(Of Integer)
        
        For Each testCase In testCases
            Dim N As Integer = testCase(0)
            Dim L As Integer = testCase(1)
            Dim pages As Integer() = testCase(2)
            results.Add(MaxBooksRead(N, L, pages))
        Next
        
        Return results.ToArray()
    End Function
End Module

Imports System
Imports System.Collections.Generic

Module QueryProcessor
    ' Processes a list of queries and prints the results
    Sub ProcessQueries(queries As String())
        Dim activePairs As New Dictionary(Of Integer, Tuple(Of Integer, Integer))()
        Dim currentPairs As New List(Of Tuple(Of Integer, Integer))()
        Dim removeSet As New HashSet(Of Integer)()
        
        Dim index As Integer = 1
        
        For Each query As String In queries
            Dim parts As String() = query.Split(" "c)
            Dim t As Integer = Integer.Parse(parts(0))
            
            If t = 1 Then
                ' Add operation
                Dim a As Integer = Integer.Parse(parts(1))
                Dim b As Integer = Integer.Parse(parts(2))
                activePairs(index) = Tuple.Create(a, b)
                If Not removeSet.Contains(index) Then
                    currentPairs.Add(Tuple.Create(a, b))
                End If
                index += 1
            ElseIf t = 2 Then
                ' Remove operation
                Dim iRemove As Integer = Integer.Parse(parts(1))
                If activePairs.ContainsKey(iRemove) Then
                    Dim pairToRemove = activePairs(iRemove)
                    removeSet.Add(iRemove)
                    If currentPairs.Contains(pairToRemove) Then
                        currentPairs.Remove(pairToRemove)
                    End If
                End If
            ElseIf t = 3 Then
                ' Query operation
                Dim q As Integer = Integer.Parse(parts(1))
                If currentPairs.Count = 0 Then
                    Console.WriteLine("EMPTY SET")
                Else
                    Dim maxVal As Integer = Integer.MinValue
                    For Each pair In currentPairs
                        Dim val As Integer = pair.Item1 * q + pair.Item2
                        If val > maxVal Then
                            maxVal = val
                        End If
                    Next
                    Console.WriteLine(maxVal)
                End If
            End If
        Next
    End Sub
End Module

Imports System

Module KazakhCurrencyComparison
    ' Dictionary to map numbers to their Kazakh words
    Private ReadOnly numberWords As New Dictionary(Of Integer, String) From {
        {1, ""},
        {2, ""},
        {3, ""},
        {4, ""},
        {5, ""},
        {6, ""},
        {7, ""},
        {8, ""},
        {9, ""}
    }

    ' Calculates the length of the som part (number word + "")
    Private Function GetSomLength(number As Integer) As Integer
        Return numberWords(number).Length + "".Length
    End Function

    ' Calculates the length of the tiyn part (number word + "")
    Private Function GetTiynLength(number As Integer) As Integer
        Return numberWords(number).Length + "".Length
    End Function

    ' Compares the lengths of som and tiyn representations
    Public Function CompareCurrencyLengths(a As Integer, b As Integer) As String
        Dim somLength = GetSomLength(a)
        Dim tiynLength = GetTiynLength(b)

        If somLength > tiynLength Then
            Return ">"
        ElseIf somLength < tiynLength Then
            Return "<"
        Else
            Return "="
        End If
    End Function
End Module

Imports System
Imports System.Collections.Generic

Module BeadProblem
    ' Calculates the minimum number of beads to remove so that only 3 distinct colors remain
    ' The input is an array of integers representing bead colors (1-4)
    ' Returns 0 if there are already 3 or fewer distinct colors
    ' Otherwise returns the minimum length of a segment containing all beads of one color
    Function CalculateMinBeadsToRemove(beads As Integer()) As Integer
        Dim distinctColors As Integer = New HashSet(Of Integer)(beads).Count
        
        If distinctColors <= 3 Then
            Return 0
        End If
        
        Dim minRemove As Integer = Integer.MaxValue
        
        ' Check for each possible color (1-4)
        For color As Integer = 1 To 4
            Dim positions As New List(Of Integer)()
            
            ' Collect all positions where this color appears
            For i As Integer = 0 To beads.Length - 1
                If beads(i) = color Then
                    positions.Add(i)
                End If
            Next
            
            Dim m As Integer = positions.Count
            If m = 0 Then
                Continue For ' Skip colors not present
            End If
            
            ' Create extended array by adding n to each position (for circular wrapping)
            Dim extended As New List(Of Integer)(positions)
            For Each pos In positions
                extended.Add(pos + beads.Length)
            Next
            
            ' Find the minimum window that contains all occurrences of this color
            Dim currentMin As Integer = Integer.MaxValue
            For i As Integer = 0 To m - 1
                Dim j As Integer = i + m - 1
                If j >= extended.Count Then
                    Exit For ' Safety check
                End If
                
                Dim startPos As Integer = extended(i)
                Dim endPos As Integer = extended(j)
                Dim length As Integer = endPos - startPos + 1
                
                If length <= beads.Length AndAlso length < currentMin Then
                    currentMin = length
                End If
            Next
            
            If currentMin < minRemove Then
                minRemove = currentMin
            End If
        Next
        
        Return minRemove
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module ArrayChecker
    ' Checks if an array can be sorted by reversing a single subarray
    ' Returns "YES" if it can be sorted this way, "NO" otherwise
    Function CanSortByReversingSubarray(arr As Integer()) As String
        Dim n As Integer = arr.Length
        If n = 1 Then Return "YES"
        
        ' Create a sorted version for comparison
        Dim sortedArr As Integer() = DirectCast(arr.Clone(), Integer())
        Array.Sort(sortedArr)
        
        ' If already sorted, return YES
        If Enumerable.SequenceEqual(arr, sortedArr) Then Return "YES"
        
        ' Find the first mismatch from the left
        Dim left As Integer = 0
        While left < n AndAlso arr(left) = sortedArr(left)
            left += 1
        End While
        
        ' Find the first mismatch from the right
        Dim right As Integer = n - 1
        While right >= 0 AndAlso arr(right) = sortedArr(right)
            right -= 1
        End While
        
        ' If the unsorted portion is smaller than the whole array, return YES
        If (right - left + 1) < n Then Return "YES"
        
        Return "NO"
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module CosineSimilarityCalculator
    ' Calculates the cosine similarity between two interest vectors.
    ' The vectors must be of the same length; otherwise, an ArgumentException is thrown.
    ' Returns 0 if either vector has a magnitude of 0.
    Function CosineSimilarity(user1Interests As Integer(), user2Interests As Integer()) As Double
        ' Validate that the two lists have the same length
        If user1Interests.Length <> user2Interests.Length Then
            Throw New ArgumentException("Interest lists must have the same length.")
        End If

        ' Compute the dot product of the interest vectors
        Dim dotProduct As Integer = 0
        For i As Integer = 0 To user1Interests.Length - 1
            dotProduct += user1Interests(i) * user2Interests(i)
        Next

        ' Compute the magnitude of each interest vector
        Dim magnitudeUser1 As Double = 0
        Dim magnitudeUser2 As Double = 0

        For Each interest As Integer In user1Interests
            magnitudeUser1 += Math.Pow(interest, 2)
        Next
        magnitudeUser1 = Math.Sqrt(magnitudeUser1)

        For Each interest As Integer In user2Interests
            magnitudeUser2 += Math.Pow(interest, 2)
        Next
        magnitudeUser2 = Math.Sqrt(magnitudeUser2)

        ' Handle the case where one of the vectors has zero magnitude
        If magnitudeUser1 = 0 OrElse magnitudeUser2 = 0 Then
            Return 0.0
        End If

        ' Compute the cosine similarity
        Dim cosineSimilarityValue As Double = dotProduct / (magnitudeUser1 * magnitudeUser2)

        Return cosineSimilarityValue
    End Function
End Module

Imports System
Imports System.Collections.Generic

Module RunningMedianCalculator
    ' Computes the running medians of a sequence of numbers using a max-heap and a min-heap.
    ' The max-heap stores the smaller half of the numbers, and the min-heap stores the larger half.
    ' The median is either the top of the max-heap (odd count) or the average of both tops (even count).
    Function ComputeRunningMedians(nums As Integer()) As String()
        Dim maxHeap As New PriorityQueue(Of Integer)(Comparer(Of Integer).Create(Function(a, b) b.CompareTo(a)))
        Dim minHeap As New PriorityQueue(Of Integer)()
        Dim medians As New List(Of String)()

        For Each num As Integer In nums
            maxHeap.Enqueue(num)
            
            ' Balance the heaps if necessary
            If maxHeap.Count > minHeap.Count + 1 Then
                Dim popped As Integer = maxHeap.Dequeue()
                minHeap.Enqueue(popped)
            End If
            
            ' Ensure the max of maxHeap is <= the min of minHeap
            If minHeap.Count > 0 AndAlso maxHeap.Peek() > minHeap.Peek() Then
                Dim maxTop As Integer = maxHeap.Dequeue()
                Dim minTop As Integer = minHeap.Dequeue()
                maxHeap.Enqueue(minTop)
                minHeap.Enqueue(maxTop)
            End If
            
            ' Calculate the current median
            Dim currentSize As Integer = maxHeap.Count + minHeap.Count
            Dim median As Double
            If currentSize Mod 2 = 1 Then
                median = maxHeap.Peek()
            Else
                median = (maxHeap.Peek() + minHeap.Peek()) / 2.0
            End If
            
            medians.Add(median.ToString("0.00"))
        Next
        
        Return medians.ToArray()
    End Function

    ' PriorityQueue implementation for VB (since .NET < 6 doesn't have PriorityQueue)
    Class PriorityQueue(Of T)
        Private _elements As List(Of T)
        Private _comparer As IComparer(Of T)
        
        Public Sub New()
            _elements = New List(Of T)()
            _comparer = Comparer(Of T).Default
        End Sub
        
        Public Sub New(comparer As IComparer(Of T))
            _elements = New List(Of T)()
            _comparer = comparer
        End Sub
        
        Public ReadOnly Property Count As Integer
            Get
                Return _elements.Count
            End Get
        End Property
        
        Public Sub Enqueue(item As T)
            _elements.Add(item)
            Dim ci As Integer = _elements.Count - 1
            While ci > 0
                Dim pi As Integer = (ci - 1) \ 2
                If _comparer.Compare(_elements(ci), _elements(pi)) >= 0 Then Exit While
                Swap(ci, pi)
                ci = pi
            End While
        End Sub
        
        Public Function Dequeue() As T
            Dim li As Integer = _elements.Count - 1
            Dim frontItem As T = _elements(0)
            _elements(0) = _elements(li)
            _elements.RemoveAt(li)
            
            li -= 1
            Dim pi As Integer = 0
            While True
                Dim ci As Integer = pi * 2 + 1
                If ci > li Then Exit While
                Dim rc As Integer = ci + 1
                If rc <= li AndAlso _comparer.Compare(_elements(rc), _elements(ci)) < 0 Then
                    ci = rc
                End If
                If _comparer.Compare(_elements(pi), _elements(ci)) <= 0 Then Exit While
                Swap(pi, ci)
                pi = ci
            End While
            Return frontItem
        End Function
        
        Public Function Peek() As T
            Return _elements(0)
        End Function
        
        Private Sub Swap(i As Integer, j As Integer)
            Dim tmp As T = _elements(i)
            _elements(i) = _elements(j)
            _elements(j) = tmp
        End Sub
    End Class
End Module

                If _comparer.Compare(_elements(ci), _elements(pi)) >= 0 Then Exit While
                Swap(ci, pi)
                ci = pi
            End While
        End Sub
        
        Public Function Dequeue() As T
            Dim li As Integer = _elements.Count - 1
            Dim frontItem As T = _elements(0)
            _elements(0) = _elements(li)
            _elements.RemoveAt(li)
            
            li -= 1
            Dim pi As Integer = 0
            While True
                Dim ci As Integer = pi * 2 + 1
                If ci > li Then Exit While
                Dim rc As Integer = ci + 1
                If rc <= li AndAlso _comparer.Compare(_elements(rc), _elements(ci)) < 0 Then
                    ci = rc
                End If
                If _comparer.Compare(_elements(pi), _elements(ci)) <= 0 Then Exit While
                Swap(pi, ci)
                pi = ci
            End While
            Return frontItem
        End Function
        
        Public Function Peek() As T
            Return _elements(0)
        End Function
        
        Private Sub Swap(i As Integer, j As Integer)
            Dim tmp As T = _elements(i)
            _elements(i) = _elements(j)
            _elements(j) = tmp
        End Sub
    End Class
End Module

Imports System

Module RobotOriginChecker
    ' Determines if the robot returns to the origin after following the sequence of commands.
    ' Parameters:
    ' s As String: A string of commands "U", "D", "L", "R".
    ' Returns:
    ' String: "YES" if robot returns to the origin, "NO" otherwise.
    Function HasRobotReturnedToOrigin(s As String) As String
        ' Initialize starting position
        Dim x As Integer = 0
        Dim y As Integer = 0
        
        ' Iterate through the command string
        For Each command As Char In s
            Select Case command
                Case "U"c
                    y += 1
                Case "D"c
                    y -= 1
                Case "L"c
                    x -= 1
                Case "R"c
                    x += 1
            End Select
        Next
        
        ' Check if robot is back at the origin
        If x = 0 AndAlso y = 0 Then
            Return "YES"
        Else
            Return "NO"
        End If
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module SeriesCalculator
    ' Determines whether a series is arithmetic or geometric and calculates the sum of the first N terms.
    ' For arithmetic series: Sn = N/2 * (2*a1 + (N-1)*d)
    ' For geometric series: Sn = a1 * (r^N - 1) / (r - 1)
    Function CalculateSeriesSum(N As Integer, series As Integer()) As Long
        Dim a1 As Integer = series(0)
        Dim a2 As Integer = series(1)
        Dim a3 As Integer = series(2)
        
        If a2 - a1 = a3 - a2 Then
            ' Arithmetic series
            Dim d As Integer = a2 - a1
            Return N * (2 * a1 + (N - 1) * d) \ 2
        Else
            ' Geometric series
            Dim r As Integer = a2 \ a1
            Return a1 * (CType(Math.Pow(r, N), Long) - 1) \ (r - 1)
        End If
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module NumberFilter
    ' Filters the given array so that it only contains numbers divisible by 3 or 5.
    ' However, if a number is divisible by both 3 and 5, it should not be included in the filtered array.
    '
    ' Parameters:
    ' arr (Integer()): The input array of integers.
    '
    ' Returns:
    ' Integer(): The filtered array containing numbers divisible by 3 or 5, but not both.
    Function FilterNumbers(arr As Integer()) As Integer()
        Dim result As New System.Collections.Generic.List(Of Integer)
        
        For Each num As Integer In arr
            Dim divisibleBy3 As Boolean = (num Mod 3 = 0)
            Dim divisibleBy5 As Boolean = (num Mod 5 = 0)
            
            If (divisibleBy3 Or divisibleBy5) And Not (divisibleBy3 And divisibleBy5) Then
                result.Add(num)
            End If
        Next
        
        Return result.ToArray()
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module DiscountCalculator
    ' Applies a discount to a list of product prices and returns the new discounted prices.
    ' Each price in the resulting list is rounded to two decimal places.
    '
    ' Parameters:
    ' prices - An array of product prices.
    ' discount - The discount percentage to be applied.
    '
    ' Returns:
    ' An array of prices after the discount is applied, rounded to two decimal places.
    Function ApplyDiscount(prices As Double(), discount As Double) As Double()
        Dim discountedPrices As New List(Of Double)
        
        For Each price As Double In prices
            Dim discountedPrice As Double = price * (1 - discount / 100)
            discountedPrices.Add(Math.Round(discountedPrice, 2))
        Next
        
        Return discountedPrices.ToArray()
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module SubsequenceSum
    ' Computes the maximum sum of all possible subsequences of length >= k for each test case
    ' t: Number of test cases
    ' testCases: Array of test cases where each test case contains a tuple (n, k) and a sequence
    ' Returns an array of maximum sums for each test case
    Function MaxSubsequenceSum(t As Integer, testCases As Tuple(Of Tuple(Of Integer, Integer), Integer())(), Optional debugPrint As Boolean = False) As Integer()
        Dim results As Integer() = New Integer(t - 1) {}
        
        For i As Integer = 0 To t - 1
            Dim n As Integer = testCases(i).Item1.Item1
            Dim k As Integer = testCases(i).Item1.Item2
            Dim sequence As Integer() = testCases(i).Item2
            
            Dim maxSum As Integer = Integer.MinValue
            
            ' Check all possible subsequence lengths from k to n
            For length As Integer = k To n
                ' Check all possible starting positions for this length
                For start As Integer = 0 To n - length
                    Dim subsequenceSum As Integer = 0
                    
                    ' Calculate sum of the current subsequence
                    For j As Integer = start To start + length - 1
                        subsequenceSum += sequence(j)
                    Next
                    
                    ' Update maxSum if we found a larger sum
                    If subsequenceSum > maxSum Then
                        maxSum = subsequenceSum
                    End If
                Next
            Next
            
            results(i) = maxSum
        Next
        
        Return results
    End Function
End Module

            Dim k As Integer = testCases(i).Item1.Item2
            Dim sequence As Integer() = testCases(i).Item2
            
            Dim maxSum As Integer = Integer.MinValue
            
            ' Check all possible subsequence lengths from k to n
            For length As Integer = k To n
                ' Check all possible starting positions for this length
                For start As Integer = 0 To n - length
                    Dim subsequenceSum As Integer = 0
                    
                    ' Calculate sum of the current subsequence
                    For j As Integer = start To start + length - 1
                        subsequenceSum += sequence(j)
                    Next
                    
                    ' Update maxSum if we found a larger sum
                    If subsequenceSum > maxSum Then
                        maxSum = subsequenceSum
                    End If
                Next
            Next
            
            results(i) = maxSum
        Next
        
        Return results
    End Function

Imports System

Module FloydWarshallAlgorithm
    ' Represents a graph for shortest path calculations
    Class Graph
        Public numOfNodes As Integer
        Public graph As Double(,)
        
        ' Initializes the graph with a given number of nodes
        ' Sets all distances to infinity except diagonal (self) which are 0
        Public Sub New(numNodes As Integer)
            numOfNodes = numNodes
            graph = New Double(numNodes - 1, numNodes - 1) {}
            
            For i As Integer = 0 To numNodes - 1
                For j As Integer = 0 To numNodes - 1
                    graph(i, j) = Double.PositiveInfinity
                Next
                graph(i, i) = 0
            Next
        End Sub
        
        ' Adds a directed edge from node u to node v with given weight
        Public Sub AddEdge(u As Integer, v As Integer, weight As Integer)
            graph(u, v) = weight
        End Sub
        
        ' Implements Floyd-Warshall algorithm to find shortest paths between all pairs of nodes
        ' Returns a 2D array of shortest distances
        Public Function FloydWarshall() As Double(,)
            Dim dist As Double(,) = DirectCast(graph.Clone(), Double(,))
            
            For k As Integer = 0 To numOfNodes - 1
                For i As Integer = 0 To numOfNodes - 1
                    For j As Integer = 0 To numNodes - 1
                        If dist(i, k) + dist(k, j) < dist(i, j) Then
                            dist(i, j) = dist(i, k) + dist(k, j)
                        End If
                    Next
                Next
            Next
            
            Return dist
        End Function
    End Class
    
    ' Wrapper function to find all pairs shortest paths in a graph
    Function FindAllPairsShortestPaths(g As Graph) As Double(,)
        Return g.FloydWarshall()
    End Function
    
    ' Helper function to convert a 2D array to a string for display
    Function ArrayToString(arr As Double(,)) As String
        Dim result As String = "["
        For i As Integer = 0 To arr.GetLength(0) - 1
            If i > 0 Then result &= ", "
            result &= "["
            For j As Integer = 0 To arr.GetLength(1) - 1
                If j > 0 Then result &= ", "
                If Double.IsPositiveInfinity(arr(i, j)) Then
                    result &= "Inf"
                Else
                    result &= arr(i, j).ToString()
                End If
            Next
            result &= "]"
        Next
        result &= "]"
        Return result
    End Function
End Module

Imports System
Imports System.Collections.Generic

Module PortraitAssignment
    ' Solves the portrait assignment problem where actors are assigned portraits based on constraints
    ' over time periods. Each actor can only be assigned a portrait when there's only one possible option left.
    Sub Solve()
        ' Hardcoded input to replace stdin reading
        Dim input As String() = {"3", "3", "2", "1", "2", "2", "2", "3", "1", "1"}
        Dim ptr As Integer = 0
        Dim N As Integer = Integer.Parse(input(ptr))
        ptr += 1
        Dim M As Integer = Integer.Parse(input(ptr))
        ptr += 1
        
        ' For each actor (by index), store the set of possible portraits
        Dim possiblePortraits As HashSet(Of Integer)() = New HashSet(Of Integer)(N) {}
        For i As Integer = 0 To N - 1
            possiblePortraits(i) = New HashSet(Of Integer)(Enumerable.Range(1, N))
        Next
        
        Dim res As Integer() = New Integer(N - 1) {}
        
        For t As Integer = 1 To M
            Dim Ki As Integer = Integer.Parse(input(ptr))
            ptr += 1
            Dim S As HashSet(Of Integer) = New HashSet(Of Integer)()
            For j As Integer = 1 To Ki
                S.Add(Integer.Parse(input(ptr)))
                ptr += 1
            Next
            
            For i As Integer = 0 To N - 1
                If res(i) <> 0 Then
                    Continue For
                End If
                
                If S.Contains(i + 1) Then
                    possiblePortraits(i).IntersectWith(S)
                Else
                    possiblePortraits(i).ExceptWith(S)
                End If
                
                If possiblePortraits(i).Count = 1 Then
                    res(i) = t
                End If
            Next
        Next
        
        ' Print the result
        Console.WriteLine(String.Join(" ", res))
    End Sub
End Module

Imports System

Module XorBasisCalculator
    ' Inserts a number into the linear basis array
    Sub Insert(x As Integer, ByRef base As Integer())
        For i As Integer = 31 To 0 Step -1
            If ((x >> i) And 1) <> 0 Then
                If base(i) <> 0 Then
                    x = x Xor base(i)
                Else
                    base(i) = x
                    Exit For
                End If
            End If
        Next
    End Sub

    ' Computes the XOR basis count for the given array
    Function ComputeXorBasisCount(a As Integer()) As Integer
        ' Compute total XOR of the entire array
        Dim totalXor As Integer = 0
        For Each num As Integer In a
            totalXor = totalXor Xor num
        Next

        If totalXor = 0 Then
            Return -1
        Else
            ' Initialize linear basis
            Dim base(31) As Integer ' 32-bit integers (indices 0-31)

            ' Compute prefix XOR and insert non-zero values into the basis
            Dim preXor As Integer = 0
            For Each num As Integer In a
                preXor = preXor Xor num
                If preXor <> 0 Then
                    Insert(preXor, base)
                End If
            Next

            ' Count the number of non-zero elements in the basis
            Dim count As Integer = 0
            For Each x As Integer In base
                If x <> 0 Then count += 1
            Next

            Return count
        End If
    End Function
End Module

Imports System

Module MinAbsDifferenceCalculator
    ' Computes the minimum absolute difference between sums of two subsets of powers
    ' using dynamic programming approach to solve the partition problem.
    Function MinAbsDifference(n As Integer, powers As Integer()) As Integer
        Dim totalPower As Integer = powers.Sum()
        
        ' canPartition(k) indicates if it's possible to get a sum of k with a subset of powers
        Dim canPartition(totalPower) As Boolean
        canPartition(0) = True
        
        For Each power As Integer In powers
            ' Traverse backwards to not reuse the same power more than once
            For i As Integer = totalPower To power Step -1
                If canPartition(i - power) Then
                    canPartition(i) = True
                End If
            Next
        Next
        
        Dim minDifference As Integer = Integer.MaxValue
        
        For s1 As Integer = 0 To totalPower \ 2
            If canPartition(s1) Then
                Dim s2 As Integer = totalPower - s1
                minDifference = Math.Min(minDifference, Math.Abs(s1 - s2))
            End If
        Next
        
        Return minDifference
    End Function
End Module
